following is variables used in the r_anlysis code.
1) x_train represents x training data set
2) y_train represent y training data set
3) subject_test represents test data subject variables

same variables replaced train with test used for testing data.

other respective variables in self explanatory form used to combine data
rbind is used to merge related x,y and subject data together

package plyr is used for easy reading of the data in table format

ddply is used to make the easy aggregate calculation (ex: averages)


